# API Archiven v2

Modern API service built with Go Echo framework and MongoDB for document archival management.

## Features

- Document storage and retrieval
- Metadata management
- User authentication and authorization
- RESTful API endpoints
- Secure file handling
- MongoDB integration
- Echo framework implementation

## Requirements

- Go 1.19 or higher
- MongoDB 5.0 or higher
- Echo framework

## Installation

```bash
go mod init
go mod tidy
```

## Configuration

1. Create `.env` file
2. Set MongoDB connection string
3. Configure application settings
4. Set server port and environment

## Usage

```bash
go run main.go
```

## API Documentation

API endpoints and documentation will be available at `/swagger` after starting the server.

